==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dimerous
<hw>Dim"er*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <grk>di-</grk>
= <grk>di`s-</grk> twice + <?/ part.]</ety> <def>Composed of, or having,
two parts of each kind.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ A <xex>dimerous</xex> flower has two sepals, two petals,
two stamens, and two pistils.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dimeter</ent>⟦br⟧
